help from people who have cat rescues plz we had a cat that my son took to his house a years ago well he has to move an the cat had to come back here were it grew up we have adult cats when we brought the old new cat in an let it out of the cage it was a fight bad and the cats we already have dont really get along well with one but never any fights just hiss at him this time the got into the fight then they went after the the one they dont like how do you get them to get along we put the new cat in a bedroom alone can we ever get them to get along an if so how i do not want any more cat fights an one get hurt how do you people who take in adult cats make them get along always always put a new cat in a safe room when you're first bringing it into the house where there is already an adult cat it will help you avoid situations like this until they get accustomed to one another now to answer your question i would leave the cat in a safe room and not let the other cats in you can take a towel or similar object and rub it on the cat that the others dont like then put that towel in your lap when you leave the room and let the other cats come and lay on your lap and pet them just get them to associate the scent of the other cat with good things like being petted etc then always monitor meetings between the cats i would only introduce one cat at a time to each other that way they can't gang up something you can try if this doesn't help over time is a product that calms cats down some are pet ease spray and comfort zone spray of diffuser these release pheromones that calm cats down and may make meetings between the cats a lot more calm Fire fighting Pet skunk Cat Hamster Ranma __ characters Pitaten Domestic rabbit Friends Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) God Emperor of Dune Dog Upholstery Socialization RuneScape quests Sauna Shaggy dog story 2000 Australian Grand Prix Spanking Mixed martial arts Menstrual cycle Dog training Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Social rule Cube (film) Hou